  "local_port": 49120,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I reschedule my appointment for passport because I put the wrong email?",
  "response": "If you need to reschedule your passport appointment because you entered the wrong email address, here\u2019s what you can do:\n\n### 1. **Log in to your account**\n   - Visit the official passport appointment website for your country (e.g., [Passport Seva](https://www.passportindia.gov.in/) for India or the U.S. Department of State website for the U.S.).\n   - Log in using your username, password, or reference number.\n\n### 2. **Update your email address**\n   - Navigate to the profile or account settings section.\n   - Update your email address to the correct one.\n\n### 3. **Reschedule your appointment**\n   - Go to the \"Appointments\" section.\n   - Choose the option to reschedule your appointment.\n   - Select a new date and time that works for you.\n\n### 4. **Check for confirmation**\n   - After rescheduling, ensure you receive a confirmation on your updated email address.\n   - If you don\u2019t receive a confirmation, contact customer support for assistance.\n\n### 5. **Contact customer support (if needed)**\n   - If you\u2019re unable to reschedule online or need help, contact the passport office\u2019s customer service.\n   - Provide your application reference number and explain the issue with your email address.\n\n### 6. **Visit the passport office (if required)**\n   - In some cases, you may need to visit the passport office in person to update your information or reschedule the appointment.\n\n### Tips:\n- Double-check your email address before saving any changes.\n- Keep your application reference number handy for quick reference.\n\nLet me know if you need help finding the specific website or contact details for your country!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
